AUDIONALS – Hackathon Targeting Reference Document

(Assistant Operating Brief)

1. What Audionals Is (Positioning Summary)

Audionals is a Bitcoin-anchored, on-chain media and application infrastructure layer, built via Stacks (Bitcoin L2).

It enables:
	•	Deterministic reconstruction of media from on-chain data
	•	Recursive composability (inscriptions referencing inscriptions)
	•	Contract-driven storage + reconstruction patterns
	•	NFT compatibility (SIP-009)
	•	Modular, chunked upload/read flows for larger payloads

This is not a speculative token project.
This is infrastructure for:
	•	On-chain media
	•	On-chain applications
	•	Composable Bitcoin-native primitives
	•	Verifiable data graphs

Tone: technical, long-term, infrastructure-first.

⸻

2. What We Want From Hackathons

Primary goals:
	•	Ecosystem visibility
	•	Technical validation
	•	Strategic partnerships
	•	Developer integrations
	•	Grant / post-hackathon funding pathways

Secondary goals:
	•	Credibility via wins or finalist placements
	•	Introductions to infrastructure teams
	•	Access to builders building on Bitcoin or adjacent ecosystems

We are not seeking short-term token hype or meme coin exposure.

⸻

3. Ideal Hackathon Characteristics

High Priority Categories
	1.	Bitcoin / Bitcoin L2 events
	2.	Stacks ecosystem events
	3.	On-chain data / storage events
	4.	Web3 infrastructure hackathons
	5.	AI x Blockchain (for deterministic media / agent memory angles)
	6.	Creator economy / NFT infra (serious, not meme-driven)

Medium Priority
	•	Ethereum L2 events (if composability narrative works)
	•	Cross-chain interoperability events
	•	Decentralized storage events (Arweave, Filecoin, IPFS)

Low Priority
	•	Pure DeFi yield events
	•	Meme coin contests
	•	Trading bot competitions
	•	Game jam events unless infra angle fits

⸻

4. Strategic Narrative Angles for Submission

When reviewing hackathons, assess whether Audionals can be positioned as:
	•	“Bitcoin-native composable media layer”
	•	“Deterministic on-chain reconstruction protocol”
	•	“Infrastructure for permanent AI memory on Bitcoin”
	•	“Recursive NFT architecture”
	•	“Contract-driven media graph system”
	•	“Composable inscription engine for Bitcoin L2”

The assistant should evaluate whether the hackathon theme allows one of these narratives.

⸻

5. What the Assistant Should Actively Search For

Search terms to use:
	•	“Bitcoin hackathon”
	•	“Stacks hackathon”
	•	“Web3 infrastructure hackathon”
	•	“On-chain data hackathon”
	•	“Decentralized storage hackathon”
	•	“AI blockchain hackathon”
	•	“Recursive NFTs”
	•	“L2 scaling hackathon”
	•	“Smart contract infrastructure hackathon”

Look for:
	•	Prize pools > $10k
	•	Sponsor-backed infrastructure tracks
	•	Post-hackathon accelerator paths
	•	Grant opportunities attached to participation

⸻

6. Evaluation Criteria (Score Each Event 1–5)

For every potential hackathon, score:
	1.	Bitcoin alignment
	2.	Infrastructure relevance
	3.	Grant/funding potential
	4.	Ecosystem prestige
	5.	Partner exposure value
	6.	Technical depth compatibility

Prioritize events scoring 20+ total.

⸻

7. Practical Constraints

The assistant must check:
	•	Timeline compatibility (4–6 week build window ideal)
	•	Remote vs in-person (remote preferred unless major event)
	•	Required chain exclusivity
	•	IP ownership rules
	•	Token issuance requirements (avoid forced token launches)

⸻

8. What NOT To Pursue

Do not shortlist events that:
	•	Require launching a new token
	•	Require custodial user models
	•	Focus exclusively on trading, yield farming, or speculation
	•	Have unclear judging criteria
	•	Have no serious technical sponsors

⸻

9. Deliverable Format for Each Recommendation

For every hackathon identified, provide:
	•	Name
	•	Organizer
	•	Dates
	•	Location (or remote)
	•	Prize pool
	•	Relevant track
	•	Why Audionals fits
	•	Risk assessment
	•	Application deadline
	•	Recommendation score (out of 30)

⸻

10. Long-Term Positioning Reminder

Audionals is positioning as:

“Boring infrastructure for permanent, composable, Bitcoin-native applications.”

Hackathons should reinforce:
	•	Infrastructure credibility
	•	Technical rigor
	•	Bitcoin alignment
	•	Ecosystem legitimacy

Not short-term hype.